        <item>
          <title>How to use the new Lock object in C# 13</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The C# programming language has provided support for thread synchronization using the lock keyword since its earliest versions. By using a lock statement, you ensure that only one thread can execute the body of the statement at a time. Any other thread is blocked until the lock is released.]]></description>
          <guid>https://majordigest.com/tech/2025/01/09/how-to-use-the-new-lock-object-in-c-13/</guid>
